   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Concerning God's Redemption</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Our learning should include the truth concerning God's redemption in type Gen 3:20-21; 4:4 and in prophecy 12:3; 22:18 .</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>In Genesis 12 and 22, God prophesied to Abraham that in him and through his seed, all the nations would be blessed.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>His seed was Christ Gal 3:16 .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>This prophecy to Abraham, according to Galatians 3, was God's preaching of the gospel to Abraham concerning His redemption v. 8 .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>At this point I would like to list more truths that we need to spend our time learning in order to prophesy.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>If you do not know the truths, you will be short not only of material but also of the proper terminology when you prophesy.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>These truths have been covered in the many messages we have spoken and printed throughout the years, so I will just list most of them here and comment briefly on some of them.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>5.</S>
